    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 7,
    "last_activity_date" : 1370605776,
    "creation_date" : 1370605776,
    "answer_id" : 16983426,
    "question_id" : 16983341,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>It is a signed type, meaning, it still has a range of 255 (as you have correctly calculated), but it starts at -128. So half the range is below zero, 1 possible number is = (zero) and the remaining 127 are above 0.</p>\n\n<p>The first bit is the sign. (1 - minus, 0 - plus)</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3608143,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 3009851,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/281bc1a4a8bea41f82f8b0c7952fc546?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "rahul",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3009851/rahul"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1384881427,
    "creation_date" : 1384881427,
    "answer_id" : 20077827,
    "question_id" : 16983341,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Range of data types\n so now we came to know that how we are calculating the Range of the  integer data types.This logic is applicable for all the integer data types.</p>\n\n<p>The full details of all the data types are given below,</p>\n\n<p>S.NO           Data Type        Bits               Ranges                                           values</p>\n\n<p>1                   boolean             1                –                                            true or false(1 or 0)</p>\n\n<p>2                   byte                    8             -128 to 127.                                    256(2^8)</p>\n\n<p>3                   short                 16         -32,768 to 32,767                       65,536(2^16)</p>\n\n<p>4                   int                      32           -2^31 to (2^31)-1                           2^32</p>\n\n<p>5                   long                   64              Refer NOTE                                     2^64</p>\n\n<p>6                   float                   32               Refer NOTE                                   ———</p>\n\n<p>7                  double               64               Refer NOTE                                  ———-</p>\n\n<p>8                   char                16              0 to 65,535                                     65,536(2^16)</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 10676147,
      "reputation" : 11,
      "user_id" : 7859585,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-WSVo-pRQorQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEc/bnfeKsLQIDY/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Manpreet Saini",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7859585/manpreet-saini"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1492049819,
    "creation_date" : 1492049819,
    "answer_id" : 43382481,
    "question_id" : 16983341,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The last bit i.e. number 8 we are writing it 2^7 is a sign bit that decides negative or positive sign so it is 2^0 +2^1 +2^2 +2^3 +2^4 +2^5+ 2^6 </p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11417693,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 8370084,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ZZLOC3r9JaM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEs/BM4THJwkjRY/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Suganth S",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8370084/suganth-s"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1502710084,
    "creation_date" : 1502710084,
    "answer_id" : 45673519,
    "question_id" : 16983341,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Bit consists of 0’s and 1’s.<strong>byte</strong> normally consists of 8 bits.so the values can be calculated using the general formula which is given below,</p>\n\n<p>no of values data type can have=<code>2^n(2 power n)</code>, where n represents no of bits.\nso the value of byte data type=<code>2^8(i.e 1 byte=8 bits)</code>,here <code>n=8</code> \nbyte value=256</p>\n\n<p>And it should be shared equal on both sides of zero ( half values at negative and half value at positive ). Hence the range for byte is from -128 to 127. </p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "user_type" : "does_not_exist",
      "display_name" : "user6235549"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 8,
    "last_activity_date" : 1533736336,
    "last_edit_date" : 1533736336,
    "creation_date" : 1510807669,
    "answer_id" : 47321833,
    "question_id" : 16983341,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Formula for Range calculation is : -2^(n-1) to (2^(n-1)-1)</p>\n\n<p>where n = no. of bits of primitive datatype.\nExample:</p>\n\n<p>For int datatype, n is 32, in short datatype, n is 16 etc.</p>\n\n<p>So, int range will be: -2^(32-1) to (2^(32-1)-1)</p>\n\n<p>By using the same formula Range of byte, short, float and double could be calculated.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6196203,
      "reputation" : 11,
      "user_id" : 4827404,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Bhf3AawU9h8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAA54/bm7kyZ11TFk/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Cute Pari",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4827404/cute-pari"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1533735820,
    "last_edit_date" : 1533735820,
    "creation_date" : 1527668123,
    "answer_id" : 50599608,
    "question_id" : 16983341,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>Formula to calculate range in Java</strong><br>\n-2<sup>(n-1)</sup> to +2<sup>(n-1)</sup>-1<br>\nWhere n is the number of bit (1 byte= 8 bit)</p>\n\n<p>So, for byte type range would be:\n-2<sup>(8-1)</sup> to +2<sup>(8-1)</sup>-1<br>\nor, -2<sup>(7)</sup> to +2<sup>(7)</sup>-1<br>\nor, -128 to +127</p>\n"
  }, {
