    "last_edit_date" : 1587005106,
    "creation_date" : 1578804247,
    "answer_id" : 59700979,
    "question_id" : 16983341,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Let's calculate range for 1 Byte</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>1 bit can take 0 or 1</li>\n<li>1 Byte = 8 Bits</li>\n<li>The first bit is used as a sign ( - or + )</li>\n<li>then remaining bits are 7</li>\n<li>so we can write 2^7 = 128 different numbers for one sign</li>\n<li>we get 0 as a positive sign. then we have 128 numbers for the negative side,127 numbers for the positive side and 0 (zero)</li>\n<li>so the range is <strong>-128 to 127 including 0</strong></li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 23736159,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 17754825,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjWs4b4sne7jPYTaPnawKA78yCqebfXNQ-eAjpe=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "Michael Gomes",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/17754825/michael-gomes"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1640341133,
    "creation_date" : 1640341133,
    "answer_id" : 70471847,
    "question_id" : 16983341,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Let's calculate range for 1 Byte in C Langauge <strong>Datatype char</strong></p>\n<ol start=\"0\">\n<li>In case of <strong>char</strong> dataype lets consider -</li>\n<li>1 Byte = 8 Bits</li>\n<li>2^8 = 256</li>\n<li>so we can write <strong>2^8 = 256</strong></li>\n<li>In case of <strong>unsigned</strong> 0 to positive integers only.\n4.1 In case of <em>signed</em></li>\n<li>we have 128 numbers for the negative side, 0 (zero) and 127 numbers for the positive side</li>\n<li>so the range is  <strong>-128 0 +127</strong></li>\n<li>Here 0 is taking one bit</li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 39330561,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 29222012,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e39c750a5fa20860242bb2c7551f93c0?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Jishnu Muraleedharan",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/29222012/jishnu-muraleedharan"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1763733670,
    "creation_date" : 1763733670,
    "answer_id" : 79826576,
    "question_id" : 16983341,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>byte - 1byte, short - 2byte, int - 4byte, long - 8byte, float - 4byte, double - 8byte, char - 2byte, boolean - decided by jvm.</p>\n<p>Formula for calculating minimum and maximum value range</p>\n<p>minimum value : -2^(n-1)</p>\n<p>maximum value : -2^(n-1) - 1</p>\n<p>n - number of bits</p>\n<p>Ex. int - 4byte = 4*8bit = 32bit, n = 32</p>\n<p>minimum value : -2^(32-1) =  -2.14748365e9</p>\n<p>maximum value : -2^(32-1) - 1 =  2.14748365e9</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 9463219,
      "reputation" : 9678,
      "user_id" : 7036419,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/66e3c04567f6d68a874c3007327c1373?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Maurice Perry",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7036419/maurice-perry"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1763734460,
    "creation_date" : 1763734460,
    "answer_id" : 79826584,
    "question_id" : 16983341,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>It is hardcoded somewhere: Byte.MIN_VALUE and Byte.MAX_VALUE.</p>\n<p>Now if you set the most significant bit to 1 and all the others to 0, you get the MIN_VALUE; decrement this value and you get the MAX_VALUE.</p>\n<p>This works for all signed integer types.</p>\n"
  } ],
